---
// The "Signing in" panel: a short explainer of the three coexisting auth paths
// (Local, GitHub OAuth, Password) that the editor at /admin/editor/ supports.
// Static content — the authoritative setup steps live in CMS_SETUP.md.
---

<section
  style="margin-top: var(--space-xl); background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-lg);"
>
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);">Signing in</h2>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-md); color: var(--color-muted); max-width: var(--text-width);">
    The editor authenticates three ways — they can coexist. See
    <code>CMS_SETUP.md</code> for the full setup of each.
  </p>
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 2;">
    <li>
      <strong>Local</strong> — open this site from a local dev server and choose “Work with
      Local Repository.” No account, no server.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>GitHub OAuth</strong> — sign in with GitHub on the live site for per-user commit
      attribution (needs an OAuth relay).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Password</strong> — a shared password backed by the Cloudflare Worker in
      <code>cms-auth-worker/</code>.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
